headline: Microsoft plans to invest $10 billion in Portuguese AI data hub
summary: Microsoft plans to invest $10 billion in artificial intelligence infrastructure at a data centre in Portugal's ​port city of Sines over the next few years, marking ‌one of the largest AI investment projects in Europe, it said on Tuesday. The technology giant ‌will work in partnership with developers Start Campus, AI infrastructure platform Nscale and chipmaker NVIDIA to deploy 12,600 next-generation NVIDIA Graphics Processing Units (GPUs) in Sines, 150 km (93 miles) south of Lisbon.

headline: CoreWeave Cuts Forecast After Delay to Customer Contract
